  "prompt": "How do I cook manchurian?",
  "response": "Manchurian is a popular Indo-Chinese dish that can be made with vegetables, chicken, or other proteins. Here\u2019s a basic recipe for **Vegetable Manchurian**, which is a vegetarian version:\n\n### **Vegetable Manchurian Recipe**\n\n#### **For Manchurian Balls:**\n1. **Ingredients**:\n   - 1 cup grated cabbage\n   - 1/2 cup grated carrots\n   - 1/4 cup finely chopped capsicum (bell pepper)\n   - 1/4 cup finely chopped onions\n   - 2-3 tbsp cornflour (cornstarch)\n   - 2 tbsp all-purpose flour (maida)\n   - 1 tsp ginger-garlic paste\n   - 1/2 tsp black pepper powder\n   - 1/2 tsp soy sauce\n   - Salt to taste\n   - Oil for frying\n\n2. **Instructions**:\n   - Mix all the grated vegetables, ginger-garlic paste, cornflour, all-purpose flour, soy sauce, black pepper powder, and salt in a bowl.\n   - Knead the mixture well to form a dough-like consistency. Add a little water if needed.\n   - Shape the mixture into small round balls.\n   - Heat oil in a pan and deep-fry the balls until they turn golden brown and crispy. Set aside.\n\n#### **For Manchurian Sauce:**\n1. **Ingredients**:\n   - 1 tbsp oil\n   - 1 tbsp finely chopped garlic\n   - 1 tbsp finely chopped ginger\n   - 1/4 cup finely chopped onions\n   - 1/4 cup finely chopped capsicum\n   - 2 green chilies, slit (optional)\n   - 1 tbsp soy sauce\n   - 1 tbsp tomato ketchup\n   - 1/2 tsp vinegar\n   - 1 tsp chili sauce (optional)\n   - 1 tsp cornflour mixed in 1/2 cup water (slurry)\n   - Salt to taste\n   - 1/2 tsp sugar (optional)\n   - Spring onions for garnish\n\n2. **Instructions**:\n   - Heat oil in a pan and saut\u00e9 ginger and garlic until fragrant.\n   - Add onions, capsicum, and green chilies. Cook for 2-3 minutes.\n   - Add soy sauce, tomato ketchup, vinegar, chili sauce, sugar, and salt. Mix well.\n   - Pour the cornflour slurry into the pan and stir continuously until the sauce thickens.\n   - Add the fried manchurian balls to the sauce and mix gently to coat them well.\n   - Garnish with chopped spring onions.\n\n#### **Serving**:\nServe hot as an appetizer or with fried rice or noodles.\n\n---\n\n### Tips:\n- For **Gobi (Cauliflower) Manchurian**, follow the same steps but use cauliflower florets instead of mixed vegetables.\n- For **Chicken Manchurian**, marinate chicken pieces (boneless or with bones) with cornflour, soy sauce, and spices, then fry or saut\u00e9 before adding to the sauce.\n\nEnjoy your Manchurian!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
